==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neurine
<hw>Neu"rine</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ney^ron</grk> a nerve.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A
poisonous organic base (a ptomaine) formed in the decomposition of
protagon with boiling baryta water, and in the putrefaction of proteid
matter. It was for a long time considered identical with choline, a
crystalline body originally obtained from bile. Chemically, however,
choline is oxyethyl-trimethyl-ammonium hydroxide, while neurine is
vinyl-trimethyl-ammonium hydroxide.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>neurin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neurism</ent>⟦br⟧
